---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Experience • Portfolio">
  <section class="section">
    <h1>professional experience.</h1>
    <p>
      8+ years of frontend development experience, 
      leading teams and delivering high-impact web applications.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="experience-header">
        <div>
          <div class="job-title">senior frontend engineer</div>
          <div class="company">tech startup inc.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="date">2022 - present</div>
      </div>
      <p>
        leading frontend development for a b2b saas platform with 100k+ active users. 
        architected and implemented a micro-frontend system that improved deployment velocity by 60%.
      </p>
      <ul class="skill-list">
        <li>reduced initial page load time from 4.2s to 1.8s through optimization</li>
        <li>established automated testing pipeline with 85% code coverage</li>
        <li>mentored 4 junior developers and conducted technical interviews</li>
        <li>collaborated with design and product teams on user experience improvements</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="experience-header">
        <div>
          <div class="job-title">frontend engineer</div>
          <div class="company">digital agency co.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="date">2020 - 2022</div>
      </div>
      <p>
        developed custom web applications for enterprise clients across various industries. 
        specialized in react-based solutions and complex data visualization projects.
      </p>
      <ul class="skill-list">
        <li>delivered 15+ client projects with 98% on-time completion rate</li>
        <li>built reusable component library adopted across multiple projects</li>
        <li>implemented responsive designs for mobile-first experiences</li>
        <li>integrated with various apis and third-party services</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="experience-header">
        <div>
          <div class="job-title">full stack developer</div>
          <div class="company">e-commerce startup</div>
        </div>
        <div class="date">2019 - 2020</div>
      </div>
      <p>
        contributed to the development of an e-commerce platform handling $2m+ in monthly transactions. 
        focused primarily on frontend development while supporting backend features.
      </p>
      <ul class="skill-list">
        <li>implemented progressive web app features for mobile users</li>
        <li>optimized checkout flow resulting in 15% conversion improvement</li>
        <li>developed admin dashboard for inventory and order management</li>
        <li>collaborated with ux team on a/b testing and user research</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="experience-header">
        <div>
          <div class="job-title">junior frontend developer</div>
          <div class="company">web development firm</div>
        </div>
        <div class="date">2017 - 2019</div>
      </div>
      <p>
        started career building responsive websites and web applications for small to medium businesses. 
        gained foundation in modern javascript frameworks and best practices.
      </p>
      <ul class="skill-list">
        <li>delivered 25+ responsive websites using modern css techniques</li>
        <li>learned react, vue.js, and node.js through hands-on projects</li>
        <li>participated in code reviews and pair programming sessions</li>
        <li>contributed to internal tools and development workflow improvements</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>education & certifications</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>computer science degree</h3>
      <p class="muted">university of technology • 2013-2017</p>
      <p>bachelor of science in computer science with focus on software engineering and algorithms.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
